com.tailf.dp.annotations

Annotation Type DpFlags


  • @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
 @Target(value=java.lang.annotation.ElementType.TYPE)
public @interface DpFlags
    Annotation class that allows to specify data provider flags to tweak the behaviour of the data provider. This annotation should be used on the class providing annotated callbacks.
    Since:
    6.5.0

    • Optional Element Summary

      Optional Elements 
      Modifier and Type Optional Element and Description
      boolean leafListAsLeaf
      Deprecated. 
      boolean noDefaults
      This parameter is used to turn off SET_ELEM and SET_CASE callbacks when a leaf or choice gets its default value due to being unset.

    • Element Detail

      • noDefaults

        public abstract boolean noDefaults
        This parameter is used to turn off SET_ELEM and SET_CASE callbacks when a leaf or choice gets its default value due to being unset.
        Default:
        false

      • leafListAsLeaf

        @Deprecated
public abstract boolean leafListAsLeaf
        Deprecated. 
        leafListAsLeaf enabled backwards compatibility mode for leaf-lists. This means that when leafListAsLeaf=true then leaf-lists are treated as leafs and not as lists, e.g. GET_ELEM/SET_ELEM calls are used rather than GET_NEXT/CREATE. This flag is deprecated and only present for backwards compatibility, and will be removed in a future release.
        Default:
        false
